   ### Minimal local fix
   
   Change the offending `memcpy` call to use the **actual size of the buffer**
   (`charFirst`) and guard the copy with a length check, ensuring we never write
   past the allocated space.
   
   ```c
   /* program.c ‚Äì line 42 (originally) */
   /* Original (buggy) */
   memcpy(structCharVoid->charFirst, SRC_STR,
          sizeof(*structCharVoid));   // <-- WRONG: copies the whole struct
   
   /* Fixed */
   size_t copy_len = strlen(SRC_STR) + 1;               // include terminating NUL
   if (copy_len > sizeof(structCharVoid->charFirst)) {
       /* Defensive handling ‚Äì abort or truncate safely */
       fprintf(stderr,
               "Error: input too large for buffer charFirst (max %zu, got %zu)\n",
               (size_t)sizeof(structCharVoid->charFirst) - 1,
               copy_len);
       exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
   }
   memcpy(structCharVoid->charFirst, SRC_STR, copy_len);   // copies *exactly* the needed bytes
   /* No extra null‚Äëterminator write needed ‚Äì it is already placed by strcpy-like copy */
